description:
1. Topology description: The structure consists of n identical dual active bridge modules connected in parallel input and parallel output (IPOP), where the switching frequency of the DAB module in each phase is consistent and the input and output filters are shared. The control signals of the switch tubes between the two-phase DAB modules are staggered 180°/n. It is worth noting that due to the half-cycle symmetry of the DAB topology, the ripple frequency of its input and output currents is twice the ripple frequency of the inductor current. Therefore, the phase shift angle of the control signal between the n-phase staggered dual active bridge modules is 180°/n
2. n can be selected as 2 or 3 (already adjusted), and more DABs can be expanded by yourself, but pi may need to be adjusted appropriately
3. Control: The output voltage PI outer loop centralized control is used to generate the sum of the currents of n DABs n*Iref. The centralized controller evenly distributes the current inner loop reference value to each DAB. The inner loop reference value of each DAB is Iref, and dual PI control is used. Input parallel output parallel IPOP mode operation
4. References, control is the control in the reference, reference: dual active bridge system analysis and design and experimental research of SiC version prototype__Su Xinpeng
5. The working conditions of the simulation setting are as follows:
Set load change: (based on the description here)
t=0.0~0.3, Ro=1; Ro=1, load is 8 ohms;
t=0.3~0.6, Ro=2; Ro=2, load is 64 ohms;
t=0.6~1.2, Ro=3; Ro=3, load is 16 ohms;
Set output voltage change:
t=0.0~0.9, Voref=200V;
t=0.9~1.2, Voref=180V;
